cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.MA 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with resource allocation and congestion control in wireless networks, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses spectrum allocation and power control, which are related to information theory and signal processing. 
3. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper proposes distributed algorithms for resource allocation, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with control of transmission powers and traffic routes, which are related to systems and control theory. 
5. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper proposes distributed algorithms for resource allocation, which can be viewed as a multiagent system.
